x4freetext: For Sb data
60 MeV Saclay electron linear
accelerator. Burst width 50 nanosec, repetition
rate 500 hz.
Photo neutrons from a natural uranium target
moderated by a polyethylene sheet.
From Knoxville Conf. 1971, vol.2, P.785.
Reference update
SD:Updated to new date formats,lower case.
Refs were swapped. The trailing zeros in values were
deleted from relevant Subents.
Time of flight, flight path = 13 m.
Low level occupation probability method.
The population of low lying states of known spin
depends on the spin of the capturing state.
The change in population is measured by taking the
intensity ratio of two low lying gamma-rays with
suitable chosen initial levels of different spins.
Primary gamma-rays populating low lying levels of
known spin give the spin of the capturing state
assuming an E1 or M1 transition. (see REL-REF)

x4freetext: Enriched sample.
Time of flight, flight path = 32 m.
Six B-10 loaded liquid scintillation
detectors with pulse shape discrimination against
gamma-ray background.
With values of gamma and 2g*gamma(n) obtained from
a transmission measurement it was possible to compare
calculated and experimental scattering areas.
Above 1 keV the area analysis technique of
Rae and block was used (E.R.Rae+,Exp. Neutr.Resonance
Spectroscopy, Acad.Press(1970)), as the resolution
function was insufficiently known.
Neutrons
Spin uncertain.
